Police in Kitale are hunting suspected thugs who killed a 43-year-old businesswoman after stealing her handbag and mobile phone. Mary Wanjiru was killed on Thursday night while on her way home after closing her Mpesa shop.  It is not clear whether she had cash on her but her friends said she might have been killed after failing to cooperate with the criminals. The woman's body was found dumped along a road by residents who alerted the police. She sustained injuries on the head. Residents have asked the county government to put up
security lights in the area. The woman's body was taken to Kitale referral hospital mortuary as police continue with investigations into the murder. Â 